<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08172c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08172c">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08172c"> 172(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in Wales sniffs Ire / Mts or clouds</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Giraldus, who seems to have been himself in Wales at the time, speaks sentimentally of the unfortunate exile <font color="green">[sc. Dermot]</font>, and describes him inhaling the scent of his beloved country from the Welsh coast, and feasting his eyes tenderly upon his own land: &ldquo;Although the distance,&rdquo; he more prosaically adds, &ldquo;being very great, it was difficult to distinguish mountains from clouds.&rdquo; <small> Emily Lawless, <a name="ELIS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ELIS"><cite title="source">Ireland (Story of Nations series</cite></a> (192?) 82</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c03032d" href="c03all.htm#c03032d">VI.C.03:032(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
